✨ Mars Gripping Primer vs e.l.f. Power Grip Primer – Do We Have a Dupe? ✨

These two primers had me shook! 😭
Applied them side by side, and from texture to performance — they’re literally copy-paste twins.

💧 Texture & Application:
Both primers have that thick, jelly-like consistency that gives you that tacky, sticky feel - the kind that holds your makeup like it owes rent. Whether it’s the OG e.l.f. Power Grip or the Mars Gripping Primer, both glide on easily and set within a few seconds.

🧲 Grip Test = PASS x2
I did the ultimate sticky test, And guess what?
Both sides gripped equally well.
No patchiness. No weird film. Just solid tackiness ready to hold your foundation all day long.

💄 Under Makeup Performance:
After blending my base on top — no difference.
Flawless finish. Smooth blending. Long-lasting wear. Literally zero difference in texture or how the makeup wore through the day.

💸 Price Check:
Now here’s where things get interesting:
🟢 e.l.f. – ₹1100+
🟢 Mars – ₹399 Almost half that (and often on discount!)
Same performance, same grip… one’s just friendlier on your bank account. 😭

⸻

⭐ Final Verdict:

If you’ve been eyeing the e.l.f. primer, but the price makes you cry a little inside,
Mars is a no-brainer.
It delivers that grip, glow, and glam without breaking the bank. Both are fab, but Mars definitely brings that “budget baddie” energy 💅

Okay so… I was super excited for this one!! 🥹💖
I’ve literally been looking for something like this in the Indian market for so long - and finally, @mruchabeauty launched their Lush Ink marker.

It’s a lip stain marker, not your regular lip liner-so don’t expect that creamy glidy formula. It’s actually a dupe for the Stila Calligraphy Lip Stain, and at just ₹389, I mean… it’s worth a try, right? (I even picked up two 😅)

✨ Super pigmented
✨ Transfer-proof
✨ Long-lasting
✨ Sets quickly – so if you want to smudge, do it fast or forget it 😬

When I tried filling it in:
• On my lower lip, it did show up, but not as evenly as I’d hoped.
• On the upper lip, it was a struggle. Barely showed up and felt patchy 💔

But to be fair, this happens with me sometimes with lip stains in general,it’s just how they behave. So if you’re planning to use it like a lipstick, maybe not. But as a stain-liner under gloss or lipstick ? Yes please.

For ₹389, it’s a decent purchase - and definitely something new and experimental for the Indian market! So if you love trying new textures and formulas, this is worth checking out. ✅
